Algerian , Malaysian firms sign $ 38 mln oil deal . Algeria ' s state - owned oil and gas firm Sonatrach and the Malaysian company Petronas Carigali signed a $ 38 million oil exploration contract on Wednesday , the Algerian official news agency APS said . Under the deal , Petronas Carigali , a subsidiary of the Malaysian state company Petronas , will carry out seismic research and sink four exploration wells , the agency said . The contract is a " production - sharing " deal , under which both companies will benefit from any commercial finds . The Malaysian firm will operate in an area northwest of Algeria ' s main oilfield , Hassi Messaoud , in the Sahara Desert . 
